title: Puerto Rico Relative Erosion Potential (REP) - 2000
name: puerto-rico-relative-erosion-potential-rep-2000
notes: The relative erosion potential is an indicator of sediment and pollution runoff from land based on slope, soil type, land cover (circa 2000) and (maximum monthly) precipitation
